      "comment_id" : 84276651,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "The return type for the count function can be found in <code>org.hibernate.dialect.function.StandardAnsiSqlAggregationFun&zwnj;&#8203;ctions.CountFunction</code> (<i>StandardBasicTypes.LONG</i>)"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 69926,
      "reputation" : 12852,
      "user_id" : 203204,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 72,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/cc47a8b461fcebd5968d0923642aa737?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Anthony",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/203204/anthony"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 42,
    "last_activity_date" : 1456219654,
    "last_edit_date" : 1456219654,
    "creation_date" : 1298117406,
    "answer_id" : 5050688,
    "question_id" : 1372317,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here is what <a href=\"http://docs.jboss.org/hibernate/core/3.5/reference/en/html/queryhql.html#queryhql-tipstricks\" rel=\"noreferrer\">official hibernate docs tell</a> us about this:</p>\n\n<p>You can count the number of query results without returning them:</p>\n\n<pre><code>( (Integer) session.createQuery(\"select count(*) from ....\").iterate().next() ).intValue()\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>However, it doesn't always return <code>Integer</code> instance, so it is better to use <code>java.lang.Number</code> for safety.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 7291708,
        "reputation" : 3651,
        "user_id" : 5557885,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 54,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/dcd35bbb6ab04c49bc1ee792e50ad1f1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
        "display_name" : "rajadilipkolli",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5557885/rajadilipkolli"
      },
      "edited" : false,
