    "last_activity_date" : 1548248168,
    "last_edit_date" : 1548248168,
    "creation_date" : 1426485190,
    "answer_id" : 29070377,
    "question_id" : 1372317,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>Long count = (Long) session.createQuery(\"select count(*) from  Book\").uniqueResult();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7291708,
      "reputation" : 3651,
      "user_id" : 5557885,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 54,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/dcd35bbb6ab04c49bc1ee792e50ad1f1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "rajadilipkolli",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5557885/rajadilipkolli"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1497166893,
    "last_edit_date" : 1497166893,
    "creation_date" : 1487104831,
    "answer_id" : 42235791,
    "question_id" : 1372317,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you are using Hibernate 5+, then query will be modified as</p>\n\n<pre><code>Long count = session.createQuery(\"select count(1) from  Book\")\n                    .getSingleResult();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Or if you Need TypedQuery </p>\n\n<pre><code>Long count = session.createQuery(\"select count(1) from  Book\",Long.class)\n                        .getSingleResult();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9668110,
      "reputation" : 131,
      "user_id" : 7174000,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/014b96a4fd83bc01310b44531a24fd2f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "LucianoDemuru",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7174000/lucianodemuru"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1521024506,
    "creation_date" : 1521024506,
    "answer_id" : 49275723,
    "question_id" : 1372317,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This works in Hibernate 4(Tested).</p>\n\n<pre><code>String hql=\"select count(*) from  Book\";\nQuery query= getCurrentSession().createQuery(hql);\nLong count=(Long) query.uniqueResult();\nreturn count;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Where getCurrentSession() is:</p>\n\n<pre><code>@Autowired\nprivate SessionFactory sessionFactory;\n\n\nprivate Session getCurrentSession(){\nreturn sessionFactory.getCurrentSession();\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1012936,
      "reputation" : 155902,
      "user_id" : 1025118,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/D9ELN.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Vlad Mihalcea",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1025118/vlad-mihalcea"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1530079883,
    "creation_date" : 1530079883,
    "answer_id" : 51055670,
    "question_id" : 1372317,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>It's very easy, just run the following JPQL query:</p>\n\n<pre><code>int count = (\n(Number)\n    entityManager\n    .createQuery(\n        \"select count(b) \" +\n        \"from Book b\")\n    .getSingleResult()\n).intValue();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The reason we are casting to <code>Number</code> is that some databases will return <code>Long</code> while others will return <code>BigInteger</code>, so for portability sake you are better off casting to a <code>Number</code> and getting an <code>int</code> or a <code>long</code>, depending on how many rows you are expecting to be counted. </p>\n"
  } ],
